01:20.448 --> 01:23.849
Now, we need to break into
your thought patterns.

01:23.851 --> 01:25.217
Hmm.

01:25.219 --> 01:28.187
Stop the symptoms
before they appear.

01:30.257 --> 01:32.424
You seem to have been
having dreams.

01:33.627 --> 01:35.794
Anxiety dreams.

01:35.796 --> 01:39.465
Not normal in the circumstances.

01:39.467 --> 01:42.301
Though there's nothing
particularly normal

01:42.303 --> 01:44.369
about these circumstances.

01:46.440 --> 01:49.475
This... is where
your thoughts are.

01:49.877 --> 01:51.443
Yes?

01:52.279 --> 01:55.614
And you are able
to describe this

01:55.616 --> 01:58.617
in more detail and accuracy
than your own bedroom.

02:04.291 --> 02:06.191
Please tell me everything.

02:08.696 --> 02:10.529
From the beginning.

04:24.598 --> 04:26.398
You're amazing.

04:31.705 --> 04:33.839
Oh, don't smoke.
They'll know we've used the room.

04:33.841 --> 04:36.742
- It's fine.
- It's not, with your concierge friend

04:36.744 --> 04:39.745
losing his job over our hookups.

04:45.753 --> 04:47.986
You're not hungry?

04:47.988 --> 04:50.555
- No, you have it.
- Raw fish.

04:50.557 --> 04:52.691
That's for you. You like sushi.

04:52.693 --> 04:54.660
We better tidy up
and get back to the bank.

04:54.662 --> 04:57.729
At bank, we get some sushi.
We can't be late today.

04:57.731 --> 04:59.564
- I've gotta leave early.
- Why?

05:02.469 --> 05:03.802
We can't keep doing this.

05:05.072 --> 05:06.905
I know.

05:06.907 --> 05:08.640
It's doing my head in, too.

05:08.642 --> 05:10.776
I keep having to buy George
Manchester season tickets.

05:10.778 --> 05:14.446
This isn't a joke.
Not for me, anyway.

05:14.448 --> 05:16.848
All right, I'm sorry. Hmm?

05:16.850 --> 05:19.484
I know I'm not sensible
as boring Ben.

05:19.486 --> 05:20.886
But we're good together, huh?

05:23.957 --> 05:25.590
Yeah.

05:25.592 --> 05:28.527
With a hour a week we get
to spend with each other.

05:28.529 --> 05:31.063
Leave Ben, and we can start
seeing each other properly.

05:31.065 --> 05:32.831
And maybe
we can even live together.

05:32.833 --> 05:36.001
Where? Your entire flat
is smaller than this bedroom.

05:36.003 --> 05:38.370
Or we can get
a bigger place together.

05:38.372 --> 05:40.739
With what? You've been
in that job seven years,

05:40.741 --> 05:43.875
- and you're still broke.
- Well, you're earning all right.

05:47.614 --> 05:50.015
I can't just leave him, Rob.

05:50.017 --> 05:52.884
We need a plan.
Thought for the future.

05:53.921 --> 05:55.520
What future?

05:56.056 --> 05:57.656
Exactly.

06:07.134 --> 06:08.934
Why're you leaving early today?

06:10.971 --> 06:12.904
We're going to a wedding,

06:12.906 --> 06:14.473
in Dorset.

06:15.509 --> 06:17.943
I do hope the weather
holds out for you.

06:18.145 --> 06:19.678
Rob...

06:22.883 --> 06:24.816
You've got a sweetheart,
you know?

06:35.162 --> 06:36.895
I'll see you at work.

06:51.745 --> 06:54.112
Bro, where've you been?
I thought we were doing lunch.

06:54.114 --> 06:56.047
Look, don't, all right?
I just got dumped.

06:56.049 --> 06:57.883
It's always something, isn't it?

06:59.620 --> 07:01.520
- Yeah.
- All right.

07:01.522 --> 07:03.688
Meet me here for dinner
after work, all right?

07:04.091 --> 07:05.524
Okay.

07:22.443 --> 07:24.075
Well, Ms. Gueller,
thank you so much.

07:24.077 --> 07:25.510
And if you'd like
to follow me...

07:30.984 --> 07:32.584
Another migraine, eh?

07:33.554 --> 07:34.886
Sarah not back from lunch?

07:34.888 --> 07:36.054
Not yet.

07:37.624 --> 07:39.424
Any calls?

07:39.425 --> 07:41.225
Yeah, Sharon from HR. She asked
if you could give her a call back.

07:41.228 --> 07:43.628
Wonder what I've done this time?

07:43.630 --> 07:45.564
- Robert.
- Hi.

07:45.566 --> 07:48.967
This young lady would like to
set up a safe deposit box.

07:48.969 --> 07:51.636
It's in the amount
of £50,000 cash.

07:51.638 --> 07:55.507
It's already been counted. She set
up the account, there's the number.

07:55.509 --> 07:57.676
Um, still waiting
for approval on this.

07:57.678 --> 07:59.644
So, let's give it off the
register for the time being.

07:59.646 --> 08:01.480
- Certainly, Ben.
- Ms. Gueller,

08:01.482 --> 08:03.682
- it's been a pleasure. All the best.
- Thank you very much.

08:03.684 --> 08:06.585
Hey. Thank you.

08:06.587 --> 08:08.887
It's a lot of cash
to be carrying around.

08:08.889 --> 08:10.755
What do I know, huh?

08:10.757 --> 08:12.023
You're a sight for sore eyes.

08:12.860 --> 08:14.659
- How are you?
- Great.

08:14.661 --> 08:17.496
Um, lemme just go
and get your receipt, okay?

08:25.906 --> 08:28.039
Uh, yeah, so we'll look
after the cash for you

08:28.041 --> 08:29.541
once all the verifications,
you know,

08:29.543 --> 08:31.176
ID, address have all been
approved, okay?

08:31.178 --> 08:32.943
Um, we'll be in contact
with you on Monday.

08:32.946 --> 08:34.645
- Okay, great. Thanks, bye.
- All right.

08:54.735 --> 08:56.668
- Robert.
- Yes.

08:56.670 --> 08:58.837
I'm leaving early today,
so if you wouldn't mind

08:58.839 --> 09:00.805
locking up the shop,
that'd be great.

09:00.807 --> 09:02.774
- Yeah, no problem.
- All right, have a good weekend.

09:02.776 --> 09:05.143
- Yeah, you too, Ben.
- Don't be long.

09:11.151 --> 09:14.052
I'm sorry about earlier.

09:14.054 --> 09:16.555
It's just... I think
you could be brilliant

09:16.557 --> 09:18.790
if you put your mind to it.

09:18.792 --> 09:20.825
- Um, Sarah...
- Let me finish.

09:22.729 --> 09:24.863
If things were different,

09:24.865 --> 09:27.065
if your situation
were different,

09:27.067 --> 09:28.767
then, maybe we...

09:29.736 --> 09:30.969
I have to go.

09:48.589 --> 09:50.322
Um, Patricia,

09:50.324 --> 09:54.092
would you, um, mind
putting away these

09:54.094 --> 09:55.660
I've just gotta go
and pack my stuff up.

09:56.597 --> 09:58.863
Please. Thanks.

10:41.241 --> 10:42.841
What're you doing?

10:43.744 --> 10:46.111
Um, I was just, uh, locking up.

10:46.113 --> 10:48.813
Have you got your stuff?
We can go.

10:49.983 --> 10:52.083
Okay, yeah. I'll just get it.

11:05.032 --> 11:06.798
You all right, Patricia?

11:06.800 --> 11:08.400
Yeah, Trish, you know,

11:08.402 --> 11:10.201
it's a bit late to get the tube.

11:10.203 --> 11:13.138
Why don't you jump on a taxi?

11:13.140 --> 11:15.373
- See you on Monday.
- Yeah, see you Monday.

11:18.912 --> 11:21.279
Hey, bruv, I think I'm coming
down with something or so,

11:21.281 --> 11:23.114
I might just slope off again,
early night.

11:23.116 --> 11:25.784
Oh, no, you don't.
Me and you are goin' for dinner,

11:25.786 --> 11:27.919
we're gonna have a catch-up.
Where'd you wanna go?

11:27.921 --> 11:29.421
Your choice.

11:30.390 --> 11:32.390
- Park Chinois.
- Come on.

11:36.463 --> 11:38.163
Well?

11:39.466 --> 11:42.701
- How's the family?
- Yes, they're good.

11:42.703 --> 11:44.969
They, uh... They ask about me?

11:46.373 --> 11:48.039
The kids do, yeah.

11:50.811 --> 11:54.012
So, uh, what about this
married woman, then?

11:54.014 --> 11:56.748
She, you know,
went back to her husband.

11:56.750 --> 12:00.085
Actually never left him.
I didn't get that far with her.

12:00.087 --> 12:02.287
Didn't make the grade.

12:02.289 --> 12:04.823
Well, you more than
made the grades.

12:04.825 --> 12:07.726
You're too good
for a situation like that.

12:08.862 --> 12:10.028
Yeah, well, it suited me.

12:11.932 --> 12:15.900
How's your financial
situation at the moment?

12:15.902 --> 12:18.870
Uh, yeah, good. Yeah,
I should be able to pay you back soon.

12:18.872 --> 12:20.939
- Everything.
- I don't care about the money.

12:20.941 --> 12:23.408
I just wanna know that you're
looking after yourself.

12:23.410 --> 12:26.244
I'm fine. I've got my job.

12:26.246 --> 12:29.013
- Got my flat. I'm okay.
- Are you?

12:29.015 --> 12:31.216
- Yeah.
- You smoke too much, you drink too much,

12:31.218 --> 12:35.787
you gamble. I can't be the
only person you owe money to.

12:35.789 --> 12:37.606
It's not like you can even
come over anymore,

12:37.607 --> 12:39.424
because you've burned every single
bridge you got with the family.

12:39.426 --> 12:42.460
You just seem to make one
bad decision after the other.

12:42.462 --> 12:45.230
- Like, dating a married woman...
- Hey!

12:45.232 --> 12:48.133
I'm not gonna stand here
and get lectured by you!

12:48.135 --> 12:50.034
Hey, I looked after you.

12:50.036 --> 12:53.505
Literally, for both Mum
and Dad when we were kids.

12:53.507 --> 12:56.274
So, just back off.
Let me make my own choices.

12:57.177 --> 12:59.177
Your mistakes, more like.

13:01.047 --> 13:03.381
Just forget dinner, all right?

13:03.383 --> 13:05.517
And go home to your wife.

13:05.519 --> 13:07.085
- Does she even know you're with me?
- Yeah.

13:07.087 --> 13:08.887
- Oh, what, she knows we're goin' to dinner?
- Yes.

13:08.889 --> 13:11.389
To the most expensive
Chinese restaurant in London?

13:13.326 --> 13:15.560
Yeah. I didn't think so.

13:16.930 --> 13:18.196
Thanks, bruv.

13:19.199 --> 13:20.265
I'll see you around.

